subSubSection.paragraph:
Distribution and habitat:
Fresh and brackish water habitats along the west coast of 
India
from near the Gulf of Kutch to Trivandrum (
Kerala
) near the southern extent of the Indian subcontinent (
Silas, 1959
; 
Talwar & Jhingran, 1991
).

Other common names for this species include thready killifish or thready top-minnow (
Talwar & Jhingran, 1991: 746
), Malabar ricefish (

Robins 
et al.
, 1991

) and Indian Glaskilli (
Seegers, 1997: 18
).
